Argo Application is a Kubernetes resource object representing a deployed application instance in an env.

It is defined two keys pieces of information:-
Source:- reference to the desired state in Git.
Destination: reference to the target cluster and namespace.

There are 3 methods to create a application
- Application declarative :- YAML

cat  /practice/application.yaml
apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: Application
metadata: 
  name: guestbook 
  namespace: argocd
spec: 
  destination: 
    namespace: guestbook
    server: "https://kubernetes.default.svc"
  project: default
  source: 
    path: gustbook
    repoURL: "https://github.com/mabusaa/argocd-example-apps.git"
    targetRevision: master 
  syncPolicy:
    syncOptions:
      - CreateNamespace=true
kubectl apply -f /practice/application.yaml
application.argoproj.io/guestbook created

kubectl get application -n argocd
NAME        SYNC STATUS   HEALTH STATUS
guestbook   Unknown       Healthy

- Web UI
- Application CLI
argocd app create app-1 --repo "" --path="" --dest-server https://kubernetes.default.svc --dest-namespace default



ofn0yfKBExWMDukU

